\cb3 n the case of rule 11, there is more than a grain of truth: buried in rule 11, there is an entire way of looking at technology, and the pace of technological change, that can revolutionize the way engineers learn technology. If it is true that every idea will be pro- posed again, then it is also true that every idea has been proposed before. If it were pos- sible to learn the basic concepts behind an idea the first time it is proposed, it should be possible to understand every new proposal grounded in the same ideas in the future.\cb1 \
